institutions of the ancient world, and in turn it can shed new light and introduce new perspectives to the challenging debate of our times on prostitution and contemporary sexual morality. The main purpose of this book is to provide the primary historical study of the topic with emphasis upon the separation of facts from the mythology surrounding the countless references to prostitution in Greek literary sources.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Mrz 2018) 0aProstitutionzGreecexHistory. 4aFrauen. 4aGender. 4aProstitution. 4aSexualität. 4agender. 4aprostitution. 4asexuality. 4awomen.0 cEPUBz978-3-11-055680-30 cprintz978311055675940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110557954423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110557954.jpg  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG